The World Energy Council (WEC) has appointed Dr Angela Wilkinson to succeed Dr Christoph Frei as CEO, effective November 1. The council stated on Monday that Wilkinson previously served as the WEC’s scenarios and business insights senior director, while being a leading global energy expert. She is also the founder and CEO of Oxford Futures and a member of two international advisory boards – the Higher School of Economics, in Russia, and the Environmental Change Institute, in Oxford, in the UK.